00:39.206 --> 00:47.115
One quiet night, a voice called his name, startling him awake in the shadows, learning to speak the words of the unseen.

00:47.175 --> 00:55.404
As he grew, the people were guided for 40 years, not always willing, but always searching.

00:56.605 --> 00:59.789
Growing in selfishness, Israel cried, give us a king.

00:59.849 --> 01:04.594
Despite the prophet's warning, the people demanded a crown.

01:04.962 --> 01:11.291
and God allowed salt to rise, tall and strong, but consumed with pride.

01:12.292 --> 01:16.498
Leading Israel in disobedience, his 40-year reign began to close.

01:17.440 --> 01:19.262
The anointing passed to another.

01:20.604 --> 01:26.292
In Bethlehem, a shepherd was chosen, a boy with a harp and a warrior's courage.

01:27.614 --> 01:33.042
David stood against the giant's roar, and with a stone Goliath fell at Israel's feet.

01:33.730 --> 01:38.835
the people saying his name in triumph and envy poison in Saul's heart.

01:40.076 --> 01:42.718
Through a wilderness in exile, David fled.

01:43.479 --> 01:49.084
Conflicts turned between anointed and rejected, chased through caves and fields of dust.

01:50.185 --> 01:52.568
