19:46.530 --> 19:49.553
And maybe it's because he cared more about what his kids thought than what God thought.

19:50.634 --> 19:53.877
But whatever that was, it led to their destruction and his.

19:54.377 --> 19:58.301
And so, just like Romans 15 says, these stories are an encouragement for us.

19:58.361 --> 20:05.528
Well, 1 Corinthians 10 says some of these stories are a warning for us that we don't do what those people did in response to God's invitation.

20:06.549 --> 20:10.693
For those who love him, obey his commands, who honor him, there's great blessing for a thousand generations.

20:10.733 --> 20:16.338
For those who reject him, ignore him, put their hand out.

20:16.642 --> 20:18.043
a judgment that's coming.

20:19.164 --> 20:20.766
Eli experiences that judgment.

20:21.066 --> 20:30.655
Now, the third character, Samuel, this little boy, who had a very young age, learned how to hear God's voice and say, your servant is listening.

20:31.436 --> 20:33.918
And God would speak to Samuel and Samuel would speak to the people.

20:34.879 --> 20:40.304
The Bible says of Samuel that when God raised him up, none of his words fell to the ground.

20:41.425 --> 20:42.046
Imagine that.

20:42.987 --> 20:46.450
All the words we use, none of Samuel's words,

20:47.074 --> 20:47.675
were wasted.

20:48.435 --> 20:52.479
And those words led to the revival of God's people and victory in battle.

20:53.880 --> 21:01.888
Samuel, he started a school of the prophets that for decades and centuries through Israel's history were the conscience of the nation.

21:01.968 --> 21:06.812
Now, maybe you've asked this question as we've gone through first Samuel, like who wrote the book first and second Samuel?

21:07.433 --> 21:09.175
Because didn't Samuel die in the very beginning?

21:09.195 --> 21:10.316
Like who wrote the rest?

21:11.597 --> 21:13.038
And that'd be a very good question.

21:13.058 --> 21:14.440
That means you're a thinking Christian, right?

21:15.541 --> 21:17.042
So scholars think that Samuel

21:17.250 --> 21:24.442
And then Nathan and then Gad, three prophets of Israel, documented the story and history of the prophets and the kings.

21:24.742 --> 21:26.966
And that's why we have the book we have today.

21:27.006 --> 21:41.169
And so Samuel's legacy lives on not just as one who spoke the word of God, but who passed it on to generations of prophets who told the stories to the people of God because we are shaped by the stories that we tell and by the songs that we sing.

21:41.810 --> 21:44.114
And if I was looking at Samuel's life,

21:44.930 --> 21:48.555
Well, you see a heart that wants to honor God in all that he does.

21:49.175 --> 21:54.923
And so as we sit here today, I'm going to ask you, do you want to be a person who honors God in all that you do?

21:57.006 --> 22:05.156
Do you want to be a person whose number one goal in life is to please God, to bring a smile to his face?

22:08.040 --> 22:09.101
It's an important question.

22:11.805 --> 22:12.786
I was talking to

22:13.506 --> 22:20.533
As somebody who's a part of our church and she's discipling this young girl and this young girl's like, so that's not me, but I want it to be me.

22:21.454 --> 22:22.335
And that's just really honest.

22:23.055 --> 22:26.178
Like, because some of you might be sitting here going like, do I want to love God and serve God?

22:26.238 --> 22:27.520
Yes, but I'd rather be rich.

22:28.581 --> 22:29.361
I'd rather be famous.

22:30.302 --> 22:31.864
I'd rather have my own company.

22:31.884 --> 22:35.868
I'd rather be this or be that, but I want to honor God first.

22:35.928 --> 22:37.149
I want that to be my number one goal.

22:37.169 --> 22:38.671
So maybe a great prayer for you as God.

22:39.071 --> 22:42.194
I want to want to honor you first in my life.

22:43.202 --> 22:49.411
And listen, if you're looking for a Bible verse like a life verse, your brand new Christian, 1 Samuel 230, those who honor me, I will honor.

22:50.092 --> 22:56.741
If that sentence defines the way you make decisions, the way you look at the world, God will bless your life beyond what you can ever imagine.

22:56.761 --> 22:59.966
I promise you, when God makes a promise, he's not going to break.

22:59.986 --> 23:08.658
He's going to keep it because for a thousand generations, he honors those who honor him, which leads us to the next

23:08.738 --> 23:13.767
character of the story, the first king of Israel, his name is Saul, and Saul starts out great.

23:14.267 --> 23:15.810
Saul is a man's man.

23:15.870 --> 23:18.495
He's a head tall than any other soldier in Israel.

23:18.795 --> 23:26.709
He's a mighty and brave warrior and humble, and God provides a great army around him, and he experiences early on some really great victories.

23:26.829 --> 23:34.482
Saul is the man, but we watch in Saul this slow descent, much like Eli.

23:35.394 --> 23:39.459
compromise, pride, and compromise shows up in his life this way.

23:39.519 --> 23:41.541
He's in a difficult situation.

23:42.322 --> 23:46.147
He has to make a decision, and God tells him to do the hard thing.

23:46.167 --> 23:50.672
Here's how he frames his decision-making.

23:51.173 --> 23:54.877
I know what God said, but I thought.

23:58.021 --> 24:00.785
Those two phrases put together can destroy your life.

24:02.126 --> 24:05.330
God said, but I thought.

24:06.818 --> 24:08.019
It seems like this is a small thing.

24:08.780 --> 24:16.409
Like I know what God says about, you know, offering my body to him and being sexually pure for faithful in marriage and chasing my singleness.

24:16.449 --> 24:20.273
I know what God says that the things I have don't belong to me so to give generously.

24:20.313 --> 24:21.074
I know what God says.

24:21.134 --> 24:23.017
I should forgive and not hold on to grudge.

24:23.077 --> 24:26.641
I know what God says, but my situation's a little bit unique.

24:26.701 --> 24:30.285
See, let me explain why what God said doesn't apply to me.

24:32.648 --> 24:34.770
We do this all the time because we're human.

24:35.906 --> 24:45.297
And because the mind has an infinite capacity to rationalize and justify why we do what we do and make it not a bad thing, that's called sin.

24:46.358 --> 24:52.526
And so we watch what seems like he's really small compromises, not waiting on God, not destroying everything God says to do.

24:52.606 --> 24:58.232
And it leads to this descent in Saul of a paranoia, jealousy of David.

24:58.813 --> 25:03.058
He starts making monuments to himself because he wants to make sure he's praised and

25:03.458 --> 25:07.784
And pride grips him to the point where it drives him mad, he ends up dying of suicide.

25:08.345 --> 25:09.967
It's a sad and sobering life.

25:10.307 --> 25:13.011
And so here's the question for, first of all, I want us to think about.

25:14.973 --> 25:17.397
It's not, is there pride in my life?

25:17.437 --> 25:20.881
Listen, if you're breathing and pride is it working your life?

25:22.864 --> 25:25.367
If there's pride in working your life, just raise your hand, okay?

25:25.387 --> 25:27.290
If you're breathing, raise your hand, same thing, same answer.

25:27.350 --> 25:30.514
The question is not, is there pride in my life?

25:30.818 --> 25:33.883
The question is, where is pride showing up in my life?

25:35.044 --> 25:36.206
See, that's what Saul does for us.

25:36.226 --> 25:36.847
He provides a mirror.

25:37.107 --> 25:38.730
Where is pride showing up for me?

25:40.633 --> 25:42.676
Maybe pride shows up in defensiveness.

25:42.736 --> 25:45.219
Where any time someone tries to tell me something, I put my wall up.

25:45.239 --> 25:46.541
What about you?

25:46.742 --> 25:47.302
That's not me.

25:47.322 --> 25:48.164
That's not what it matters.

25:48.204 --> 25:53.592
And no one can tell you anything because the walls are so highly erector.

25:53.652 --> 25:55.154
Maybe for you, it's

25:55.362 --> 25:57.966
Every conversation someone starts, you turn it into you.

25:58.006 --> 25:59.890
Well, let me tell you about me and blah, blah, blah, blah.

25:59.910 --> 26:10.708
You have this like, you know, all these words about you and all the conversations who always turn to you or maybe, maybe pride is manifest in your life and all this stuff is mine.

26:10.728 --> 26:11.409
I don't want to share it.

26:12.651 --> 26:15.896
Maybe pride is manifest in your life for you.

26:16.698 --> 26:21.746
Overcompensate for your inadequacies like solved it and try to make yourself someone you're not.

26:22.306 --> 26:37.308
And so your public life and your private life are getting more and more distant from each other because pride forces you to keep up the image, that image where on social media, it looks like the perfect light, but you know, under the scenes and God knows it is not the same person.

26:37.369 --> 26:46.582
Listen, wherever pride is at work and pride is at work in your life, be cautious because we can see pride in everyone else's life except our own.

26:47.684 --> 26:51.730
And this is why we need God's word and good friends to teach us and show us

26:52.162 --> 26:55.868
who we are and how we are living our life.

26:56.569 --> 26:59.433
And then the final person we see in First Amazon is David.

26:59.473 --> 27:01.576
He's the one that is most famous in the story.

27:01.616 --> 27:03.139
He's the little boy that kills the giant.

27:03.179 --> 27:12.193
He's the one who has maybe a difficult childhood forgotten by his dad, rejected by his brothers, the little punk kid, the nobody kid who rises all the way to the throne.

27:12.233 --> 27:14.857
He's like the guy we love to cheer for, the underdog.

27:14.877 --> 27:18.082
And he's described as a man after God's own heart.

27:19.384 --> 27:20.946
But David also stumbles.

27:21.506 --> 27:22.747
and falls and disappoints us.

27:22.767 --> 27:30.056
He makes promises that he does not keep, but there's something about David that knows how to respond to those moments and repent and humble himself.

27:30.096 --> 27:34.761
He knows he deserves the judgment of God, but he constantly throws himself on the mercy of God.

27:35.922 --> 27:41.369
And there's a moment in David's life where David says to God, God, you've done so much for me.

27:41.509 --> 27:42.770
I wanna build you a house.

27:42.830 --> 27:43.791
I wanna build you a temple.

27:44.172 --> 27:47.355
And God says to David, no, you're not gonna build me a house.

27:48.136 --> 27:49.618
I'm gonna build you a house.

27:50.498 --> 28:02.498
And the house I'm going to build you is you're going to have descendants after descendants after descendants and the line of your Kingly reign and legacy will never end.

28:04.641 --> 28:08.628
What is God saying?

28:08.648 --> 28:14.738
A love, a faithful love that will last from generation to generation.

28:15.458 --> 28:16.359
Now here's what happens.

28:16.499 --> 28:21.884
Next, David dies and Solomon, his son reigns and all these different kings raise and a lot of them do some really evil things.

28:22.685 --> 28:26.229
And there's a phrase that follows in the book of kings and chronicles.

28:27.009 --> 28:34.777
And it's a phrase to describe the judgment that should be happening to the kings that doesn't happen because of David.

28:34.997 --> 28:38.901
117 years after David, there's a descendant of David named Johorim.

28:39.041 --> 28:40.623
And Johorim is doing wicked and evil things.

28:40.703 --> 28:43.986
And look at God's response to the judgment on

28:44.194 --> 28:55.968
Jerusalem, he says, yet the Lord would not destroy Judah for David, his servant's sake, as he promised him to give him always a light and to his children.

28:57.890 --> 29:01.534
For David's sake, God promised.

29:02.075 --> 29:11.826
No matter what happens next, I will not remove my favor over this nation or my promise over David, because when God makes a promise, he always keeps it.

29:13.154 --> 29:19.020
This is what you call a long legacy.

29:19.900 --> 29:22.063
Hannah has a long legacy.

29:22.143 --> 29:24.785
Her songs are still being sung today.

29:24.805 --> 29:30.831
Samuel has a long legacy of leading schools of prophets who continue to speak prophetically into the church.

29:30.851 --> 29:37.557
David has a long legacy, 117 years after he dies.

29:38.198 --> 29:42.482
His influence is still being felt in the fifth generation of Israel's

29:42.818 --> 29:43.199
nation.

29:44.560 --> 29:57.218
So the question that I've been thinking about and something I read this week that's been rattling through my brain is, am I the type of person who's honored my ancestors and blessed by descendants?

29:58.419 --> 30:09.234
You know, if we're in this place between one generation and we're before us and all the lessons we can learn and we're about to pass our faith on to the next generation, do I have a way, have I found a way to honor

30:10.274 --> 30:14.119
the heart and mind and faith of people like Hannah, Samuel and David.

30:14.139 --> 30:21.809
By taking all that and incorporating into my life as I follow Jesus, and then have I taken, and am I blessing my descendants to the third and fourth generation?

30:21.829 --> 30:23.131
Am I thinking past myself?

30:24.673 --> 30:31.161
You see, because as we look through the book of First and Second Samuel and we ended, the story of First and Second Samuel does not end there.

30:32.283 --> 30:37.810
You see, Jesus would say a thousand years after these moments, he would say, you know, all those stories, they point to me.

30:38.882 --> 30:41.305
The song that Hannah wrote, there's points in me, the anointed king.

30:41.345 --> 30:47.794
The promise that God made to David about the legacy and the king, the anointed one that would come from his legacy that's talking about me.

30:47.834 --> 31:01.713
You see, God knew through the history of time that at the perfect moment he was gonna answer the prayers of Hannah and the prayers of Samuel and the prayers of David for the nation that he was gonna fulfill the promise that he made to Moses on that mountain.

31:01.933 --> 31:08.242
I am the God who shows a faithfulness to a thousand generations and he did that in the coming of Jesus.

31:08.706 --> 31:22.822
Galatians 4, when the set time had fully come, God sent his son, born of a woman, born under the law, to redeem those under the law that we might receive adoption to sonship.

31:24.503 --> 31:32.512
God demonstrates his love for us, that while we were still sinners, he sent his son Jesus to die in our place.

31:32.752 --> 31:35.315
Aren't you grateful for the goodness of God, the faithfulness of God?

31:35.335 --> 31:37.778
He is faithful even.

31:37.954 --> 31:40.117
when we are not.

31:40.457 --> 31:43.140
And so God's faithful for a thousand generations.

31:43.160 --> 31:49.427
And we've been talking about all these stories because the Bible says that one generation should commend the works of God to the next generation.

31:49.467 --> 31:51.850
And so we've been telling God stories for the last 40 days.

31:51.890 --> 32:02.002
And I want to share with you just in a very practical way, the way that faith is being passed on to the next generation, the heart of worship, the heart of Hannah writing this song of gratitude.

32:02.754 --> 32:10.624
You see, behind this wall, there's a group of middle school and high school students who are praising God and learning God's word and learning to share their faith.

32:10.704 --> 32:20.577
And on this side of the wall, there's Calvary Kids, our young kids learning how to sing songs and learn God's word and do all the things that it means to honor God in their life.

32:20.637 --> 32:22.680
And there's a leader on this side of the wall, her name is Gabby.

32:23.561 --> 32:26.465
And she doesn't just lead our kids and praise and worship every week.

32:26.805 --> 32:30.610
She leads teams to know and follow Jesus.

32:30.818 --> 32:37.347
Gabby said to a young girl, Ariana, in eighth grade, hey, I want you to help us teach the kids and Ariana has this idea.

32:37.507 --> 32:41.993
She said, hey, what if we teach the kids, like in fourth and fifth grade, how to write their own songs?

32:43.195 --> 32:43.996
Like, who does that?

32:44.076 --> 32:45.879
Well, that's the idea coming from an eighth grader.

32:45.959 --> 32:53.068
And so she teaches the kids how to write some of the songs and listen to Mo, a fifth grader song that she wrote.

32:54.650 --> 33:00.178
When I feel sad, Lord, you help me feel better and give me signs that it's, oh,

33:00.514 --> 33:02.357
Okay.

33:02.377 --> 33:13.413
Faith being formed in a young girl who knows in the bigness of the universe, God sees her sadness and will make it, okay, that's how faith is formed.

33:13.794 --> 33:16.718
Listen to Harper's song.

33:16.738 --> 33:18.841
I will praise you because you are powerful.

33:18.861 --> 33:20.624
All creation praises your name.

33:21.004 --> 33:23.788
Every minute you show us your power through the smallest things.

33:24.730 --> 33:27.534
You are so glorious, your love never fails.

33:28.435 --> 33:30.418
I will praise you till the end of my

33:30.626 --> 33:30.986
days.

33:32.969 --> 33:45.102
Harper, this young girl, can see that in all of the bigness of God's creation that he is worthy of praise, but in the smallest things, he is intimately involved in details of life.

33:45.122 --> 33:47.945
Hannah sang that song and now Harper singing that song.

33:48.826 --> 33:56.114
And I want to tell you another story of a woman like Hannah named Olga who prayed for her son who was far from God.

33:56.578 --> 34:02.144
And how God heard the cry and the prayer of this mom, our God is faithful from generation to generation.

34:02.205 --> 34:03.806
Take a look at Olga's story.

34:09.653 --> 34:15.660
So I can remember at a young age, my parents would be fighting and it would get pretty hectic, pretty wild at times.

34:15.960 --> 34:20.786
During Christmas, my mom and my dad came to me and they basically told me we're gonna get divorced.

34:23.842 --> 34:27.167
At this time, I'm just getting ready to start high school.

34:28.229 --> 34:32.014
And so this was probably one of the most traumatic experiences for me as a kid.

34:32.134 --> 34:33.777
He was my only biological child.

34:34.758 --> 34:40.607
I had helped raise three brothers before him, the youngest 12 years apart from him.

34:41.248 --> 34:43.111
So he was like my china doll.

34:43.251 --> 34:47.016
And I spoiled him deliciously and unapologetically.

34:47.457 --> 34:48.258
He was obedient.

34:48.338 --> 34:49.160
He was loving.

34:49.180 --> 34:50.862
He was a great student.

34:51.323 --> 34:53.426
I mean, you know, I don't have

34:54.050 --> 34:56.573
and a major trauma when he was young.

34:56.994 --> 34:59.417
Until his father and I started having problems.

34:59.477 --> 35:03.903
And then he sensed that there was something very wrong going on in the house.

35:04.584 --> 35:06.847
And so that's when he just changed.

35:07.988 --> 35:09.851
I began to hang out with guys much older than me.

35:10.311 --> 35:14.396
Guys that were involved in drugs and kind of gang stuff.

35:14.416 --> 35:16.119
And they became my family.

35:16.920 --> 35:20.024
And that became kind of my pattern across my high school years.

35:20.625 --> 35:21.746
There was a lot of

35:21.954 --> 35:23.056
violence during that time.

35:23.096 --> 35:24.098
I was getting arrested.

35:24.960 --> 35:26.904
My anger became directed at my family.

35:26.924 --> 35:29.309
I was mad at my mom and my dad.

35:29.930 --> 35:31.333
They had basically ruined my life.

35:31.914 --> 35:35.280
So I became extremely angry, bitter.

35:36.242 --> 35:39.849
You know, you would never see me smile, especially with my parents.

35:39.869 --> 35:42.194
You know, I just have walls up with them.

35:42.530 --> 35:44.852
I went to UCF to get a finance degree.

35:45.072 --> 35:49.977
My mom thinks, oh, he's doing great, he's getting his finance degree, and really I'm just running drugs.

35:50.478 --> 35:54.041
I'm also taking classes, but again, I'm doing well, I'm passing.

35:54.562 --> 36:04.291
And my mom and my stepdad, I think, were able to see that from afar, and that whole time just continued to pray for me and love on me.

36:04.311 --> 36:11.058
It was always the letters that I remember the most that would tell me they were praying for me.

36:11.138 --> 36:16.746
You know, I think when you read the Bible, you see Paul, he's always telling the church, it's like, hey, I'm praying for you.

36:16.786 --> 36:17.446
I'm praying for you.

36:17.767 --> 36:20.571
But they prayed persistently.

36:20.591 --> 36:21.973
And it was never judgy.

36:22.073 --> 36:22.653
It was never.

36:22.954 --> 36:24.256
When are you going to start going to church with it?

36:24.276 --> 36:25.157
It was never that.

36:25.277 --> 36:27.941
It was always like, hey, you want to come to church with us?

36:28.381 --> 36:28.942
And I'm like, no.

36:29.703 --> 36:32.907
I wasn't aware of what he was doing until he came home.

36:32.967 --> 36:36.652
That's when we realized that there was a lot wrong.

36:38.114 --> 36:40.978
And I know that every night he went to the clubs every night.

36:41.602 --> 36:51.258
And we knew that, but the Lord was so gracious and just continued to impress on both of us that we were not to say, you know, you shouldn't be there, you shouldn't be doing this.

36:51.318 --> 36:52.500
This is what you should be doing.

36:53.742 --> 37:02.997
It was really remarkable because that would be my norm to explode and to explain that you are doing something wrong and it's going to be bad and you need to go to church.

37:03.458 --> 37:06.002
But the Lord never impressed on us to do that.

37:06.210 --> 37:13.640
You know, I would come home on Saturday nights and be in my room and I would watch a show, a guy called Howard Stern.

37:14.501 --> 37:21.210
And at the end of the Howard Stern show, the very next show was Calvary Chapel, Bob Koi that would come on.

37:21.230 --> 37:23.613
And I'm like, oh, that's the church that we go to.

37:23.654 --> 37:25.756
And I sit there and I listen to Bible studies.

37:26.057 --> 37:28.160
So God was just really softening my heart through that time.

37:28.300 --> 37:30.883
And then I eventually end up going to a Tony Robbins conference.

37:31.264 --> 37:35.890
He had said this phrase, if there's something you know you need to do, don't put it off.

37:36.418 --> 37:39.301
It was in that moment that the light switch went off.

37:40.383 --> 37:45.669
That everything that I had been hearing for all these months going to church, I realized that I wasn't right with God.

37:46.190 --> 37:48.753
And the other thing that hit me was, I'm not gonna live forever.

37:48.793 --> 37:55.221
And so for whatever reason in that moment, God decided to kind of make those two truths extremely heavy on me.

37:55.401 --> 37:57.864
I realized who Jesus was.

37:58.665 --> 38:02.610
I realized why he came and that it was for me personally.

38:02.650 --> 38:06.194
It wasn't just for my crazy parents or crazy Christians.

38:06.434 --> 38:09.938
In that moment, it all just came together in an instant.

38:09.958 --> 38:14.003
And one of the things that I eventually settled on is like, all right, I'll go to church.

38:14.484 --> 38:20.691
I was coming downstairs and I was in a hurry to get to church on time, and Chris is at the bottom of the stairs.

38:20.992 --> 38:22.574
And he says, are you going to church?

38:23.695 --> 38:25.037
And I said, yeah, I am.

38:25.918 --> 38:26.779
And he said this.

38:26.859 --> 38:27.980
He said, can I go with you?

38:28.020 --> 38:29.322
And I almost passed out.

38:29.562 --> 38:32.786
The pastor was saying that he was

38:33.154 --> 38:40.467
near the end of his sermon and that he was going to ask if anybody wanted to come forward and give their lives to Christ.

38:41.489 --> 38:50.245
And Chris immediately jumps up out of his seat and he runs, not walk, but runs really fast to get up to the front.

38:50.566 --> 38:52.049
And so I was stunked.

38:52.169 --> 38:55.375
I was, you know, I think I got up out of my chair.

38:55.455 --> 38:57.138
I went up there and put my hand on him.

38:57.634 --> 39:02.600
I realized that if I'm going to do this following Jesus thing, I need to give it my all.

39:02.820 --> 39:08.447
And basically, for a year, I asked Tom, I said, hey, I just want to know everything that you know about the Bible.

39:08.547 --> 39:09.768
Would you teach me?

39:09.788 --> 39:11.770
And he would just do Bible studies with me.

39:12.051 --> 39:14.834
He would gently correct me when he would see me straying.

39:15.234 --> 39:17.697
He gave me the foundation, I think, for my walk.

39:20.160 --> 39:23.324
It was through serving that I think I discovered.

39:23.424 --> 39:25.266
I mean, I think I can teach

39:25.570 --> 39:43.218
pastor Mike this year came to me I had been serving at that time in high school ministry and he said hey there's a there's a position that's opening up it's not a Fort Lauderdale it's it's part-time but it's at our new plantation campus would you want to take it and I'm like absolutely so I jumped in part-time

39:43.298 --> 39:46.083
on staff at Calvary Plantation as the youth pastor.

39:46.323 --> 39:52.274
